cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper discusses the use of activation functions in multilayer perceptrons (MLP) and their application in generalized learning vector quantization (GLVQ), which are both subfields of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with classification and regression learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, GLVQ is a prototype-based classification learning method, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of activation functions in image classification (cs.CV) and their influence on performance (cs.SD - Sound and Music Computing).
